void BoUpSLP::reorderTopToBottom() {
...
  // Reorder the scalars.
  combineOrders(Shuffle, Order);
...
}
```
Here, `P2` is `Order`. `Order` is a member of `BoUpSLP` of type `SmallVector<unsigned, 16>`. It is populated in `BoUpSLP::buildTree`.

The problem description mentions horizontal reduction. The stack trace includes `HorizontalReduction::tryToReduce`. This suggests the issue is related to how horizontal reductions are handled.

