```
This will give me the line number. Then I'll find the call to `getReductionOrder`.

The relevant code snippet in `tryToReduce` is:
```cpp
  if (Rdx->isOrdered()) {
    SmallVector<unsigned, 16> Order;
    Rdx->getReductionOrder(Order);
    Builder.setHorRdxOrder(Order);
  }
```
I need to add `Order.resize(VF.getKnownMinValue());` before `Rdx->getReductionOrder(Order);`. `VF` is available in this function as `Builder.getVF()`.

```cpp
  if (Rdx->isOrdered()) {
    SmallVector<unsigned, 16> Order;
    Order.resize(Builder.getVF().getKnownMinValue());
    Rdx->getReductionOrder(Order);
    Builder.setHorRdxOrder(Order);
  }
```
This seems correct. It ensures that the `Order` vector has the correct size before it's populated by `getReductionOrder`. This prevents `combineOrders` from accessing out of bounds when using this `Order` vector.

